World War II bomber pilot, who flew Concorde 002 out of Filton Airport in Bristol, England.

00:08:35.856 --> 00:08:40.216
Now, in order to have a plane that travels at the speed of

00:08:40.216 --> 00:08:45.916
sound, engineers couldn’t just use the same old aircraft designs.

00:08:46.236 --> 00:08:50.366
They actually had to make some rather large innovations.

00:08:51.496 --> 00:08:58.396
One of the most notable was the plane’s nose, the bit at the front of the plane.

00:08:59.836 --> 00:09:05.966
