00:18:19.839 --> 00:18:24.149
out to be the result of a chain of small but fatal errors.

00:18:25.009 --> 00:18:29.889
The first of these errors took place before the flight even took off.

00:18:31.429 --> 00:18:36.339
To start with, the plane was over its maximum structural weight.

00:18:36.969 --> 00:18:42.219
Not only had the plane been overfueled, there was too much fuel put in it,

00:18:42.219 --> 00:18:47.939
but more items of baggage were placed in the hold than were planned for.

00:18:49.189 --> 00:18:51.849
Put simply, the plane was too heavy.

00:18:53.099 --> 00:18:57.389
The next part sounds a little bit like a freak accident.

00:18:58.209 --> 00:19:04.499
Just after Flight 4590 had begun taxiing down the runway, a short strip of

00:19:04.499 --> 00:19:09.309
metal fell off of the engine of another plane travelling down the same runway.

00:19:10.569 --> 00:19:16.219
